cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing incentives to improve the performance and engagement of crowd workers on a microtask-based annotation platform. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques to identify named entities in a stream of Twitter posts. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the fairness and interest of the overall experience for crowd workers. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper involves the use of crowdsourcing to annotate social media data. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses a mathematical model (continuous-time Markov chain) to analyze the performance of crowd workers in contests.
